bilities. We believe so strongly in education and provide a ton of in-house training, teaching and coaching. You will work directly with both co-owners of the business and have the opportunity to help grow this business even further by serving our clients with an incredible experience. You have the potential to have a job that is more then just a job, but a place where you can really grow personally, professionally while truly improving peoples lives. We are looking for a candidate to help us grow the revenue of the clinic by retaining the clients that we have. This person will also be able to convert any new interest that comes to us as a result of the goodwill or word of mouth that already exists in our community. Doing this will involve developing deep and meaningful relationships with our clients, handling objections, spending time getting to know each one personally and answering their concerning questions about physical therapy & what we do. We need this person to create the type of experience that customers cant wait to come back to, will be happy to pay for and be just as happy to tell others about. Demand for this role has been high and we invite you to apply if you feel confident and able to achieve the tasks and responsibilities listed below: We know true \u201cA players\u201d love to be held accountable for high standards of performance, which means you will be given your own key objectives and outcomes to meet (with support & training). When these are consistently met, you\u2019ll experience benefits and privileges. To achieve the level of success we are looking for, you will be required to: A. The mission of the company is to \u201chelp people make better decisions\u201d, and one of the things that we offer our prospective patients to help to do that is give them time up front requiring you to hold a lengthy (at least 15-25 minute) conversation with new clients on the phone, ensuring clients are committed and objections addressed to communicate the value of our services (on the phone and in person) and be able to explain how what we do is worth the price we are asking Your \u201cwarm lead conversion\u201d rate \u2013 1 of the responsibilities of this position will be your ability to effectively communicate to our potential patients the benefits of physical therapy so they can \u201cmake better decisions about their health\u201d. We expect you to convert 8 out of 10 (or 80% ). It will be expected you to become proficient at this within 3 months (with training). B The biggest responsibility of this position is to retain clients. We know if we provide a world class waiting room environment for our clients, one they will look forward coming back to, they will. We expect you to be able to build relationships with our clients and from the moment they pull up to our building you are focused on brightening their day. You will be required to be pro-active in retaining clients and part of that requires you to be able to communicate our services, upcoming sales & products, knowing if you do provide this type of waiting room experience 8 out of 10 current clients (or 80%) will keep coming back for more. C. Ensure people show up excited for their first appointment after scheduling and continue to be throughout their plan of care, so much so that they will return and become lifetime clients. Patients who book appointments and then \"no show or cancel\" are not good for either parties involved. Because of that, You will be required to have an arrival rate of 90%, and a re-schedule rate of 90% for drop offs within 30 days. D. Contribute and attend 3 hours per week in house training \u2013 including giving a once per month power point presentation to the rest of the team about client experience or core values - and attend a minimum of 30 hours per year SELF FUNDED education to improve your knowledge in your role. This includes learning, reviewing metrics from previous week and working on improving areas that fall below standards set and role playing, coaching and training. As well as, bring new ideas and ways to improve customer experience based on feedback and experience in the position. E. Be flexible in your working hours - In the 21st Century, patients expect to be seen before, during, after work and on weekends. We know that back pain doesn\u2019t go away for our patients after 5pm. Because of that, and to be successful in this role, you will be required to make yourself available from 7am until 7pm Mon-Fri and Saturday mornings from 8am \u2013 12pm. Your 30-40 hours per week contracted hours will be scheduled during these hours (start and end times between these hours are negotiable!) and the salary ($40,000-$46,000) agreed upon will compensate you for making yourself available during these hours of standard business operation. F. Drive referrals \u2013 within 3 months we expect that at least 3 WOM referrals are calling in due to you being pro-active with our current clients to drive referrals from their families, friends or co-workers (and within 6 months at least 4 WOM referrals) and be pro-active in asking for reviews on google/FB (15 per month). G. Be dependable, on time, willing to do things because they need to be done without thinking \u201cthat\u2019s not my job\u201d or \u201cthat\u2019s not why I was hired\u201d. Your presence alone illustrates your commitment to being a team player and making EVERYONE\u2019S experience better, either team mate\u2019s or client\u2019s & contriubtes to the fun environment we all want to work in. Communicate with PTs to keep people on schedule, discuss when POC is coming to an end (purchase another package if appropriate), relay if someone is unsatisfied, etc. Effectively communicate to keep clients happy and coming back for more. I. You will be responsible for front desk type tasks that keep the business running effeciently (knowing details, organization, time management, schedule efficency & maximazation make the biggest difference ) including things like: Develop and regularly update the procedure library so that every aspect of the role is documented, ensuring it can be achieved by someone else in the business. Coordinating front desk activity, organizing, providing receipts, taking payments, creating super-bills, handwriting cards, running errands, intake paperwork, tracking/inputting data etc. Be proficient with computers, smart phones, software such as word, excel, powerpoint, google drive, sending and receiving email, managing a computer either PC or MAC. Take pictures/videos with clients and employees Send/give appropriate items in customer journey 100% of the time Know when big things are happening in clients lives, plan for them and \u201cwow\u201d clients (ie birthdays, retirement, etc. ) Furthermore, Experience in this exact role is not required and neither is a degree from a college/university, however the candidate is required to adhere to the following core values: Deliver \u201cWOW\u201d through service Embrace & Drive Change Create Fun, Positivity & Laughter Be Creative & Open Minded Constant Pursuit of Growth & Learning Person First, Patient Second Build Open & Honest Relationshiops With Communication Build a Positive Team & Family Spirit Do More With Less \"Walk the Talk\" Be Humble Be Kind, Energetic & Empathetic The successful candidate will work for the owners of the business ( Annie & Brooke) to ensure that these core values are present in the day to day running of the business \u2013 and ultimately, responsible for the successful growth of the business... All hiring (and firing) at The Physio Revolution is made with these Core Values firmly in mind and we look forward to discussing them more with you at the interview - when we can also discuss other benefits and incentives of you choosing to join our team! It is said that some of the happiest & most fulfilled people in the world, possess 2 things an insatiable appetite for growth and learning & an ability to serve others to the utmost of their abilities. We believe that whole heartedly and is why we put such a strong emphasis on serving our clients to the best of our abilities while constantly pursuing more growth and learning. We will support you in this role and can provide an incredible career opportunity- one where you will have the potential for growth in the company and where pay rises and privileges will be linked to performance. If you are a friendly & fun person who likes what you have just read & looking for a learning environment where you can grow yourself professionally & personally\u2026then YOU should apply via the link below! We look forward to talking to you soon! Please Apply here: https://thephysiorevolution.lpages.co/frontdeskhire/ It has next steps in our hiring process : ) Job Type: Full-time Salary: $40,000.00 to $45,000.00 /year Job Type: Full-time Pay: $40,000.00 - $45,000.00 per year Experience: Customer Service: 1 year (Preferred) Customer Retention: 1 year (Preferred) receptionist: 1 year (Preferred) in bound Sales: 1 year (Preferred) Education: High school or equivalent (Preferred) Work Location: One location Setting: Other Ergonomic Workspace: Yes Schedule: Other Company's website: thephysiorevolution.com Work Remotely: No "
